	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=167542><span id=Scholar>jamosb</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>52 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.55]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>you will not see a power increase if the stone is not in a charm..hint if your in your 20s get a wayfarers charm as soon as you get 6 adv points..put the adv stone in it at the pool as soon as you get it..talk to one person in the camp he will give you information (after a while you may have to seek others outside the camp for more stat increases)..after 10 successes you will get a stat increase in your stone after you talk to the right person (have to open up the charm then click on the aug item in the picture to see the stat increases). Warning this happened to me, and i think its a bug..if you dont have the stone in a charm when you get <br>&quot;the your stone has increased in power message&quot; it will not increase stats and hence you have to do 10 more adv and then have the stone in the charm to get the message again and it will work then..ie doenst keep track if the stone is just in your inventory. it is every 10 adv in one theme dont let anyone tell you different. I hailed a gm on this as i was having the above problem he asked if I completed 10 adv at the same camp. It was his opinion that it was a bug that it doesnt give stat increases if you dont have the stone augmented in a charm (yes even after you put it in a charm the stat increases do not show up). Also the type of adventures (assinate, collect, slaughter, etc.) doenst matter its just if you completed it succesfully. <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jan 14 08:49:56 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
