	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=250051><span id=Scholar>Anglish</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>51 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.38]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>At level 40, I got my 10th win in Rujark and I started to see stats finally. This means you do NOT have to be level 65 to see your stats, which some people thought with the Recommended Level on the stone. I also had 2 wins in Mistmore and 5 in Takish at the time, but did not get any stats until my 10th win in Rujark. This seems to verify that <i>the first set of stats come after 10 wins in any one camp</i>, and you don't have to be 65.<br><br>I got BOTH of the following messages after hailing Barstre Songweaver after the 10th success:<br><br><span style='color: yellow;'>You have received an invaluable piece of information!<br>Your Adventurer Stone glows with more power as you gain stature with the Wayfarers Brotherhood.</span style='color: yellow;'><br><br>The second sentence comes when you actually get new stats on your stone.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Dec&nbsp;&nbsp;3 13:51:51 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br><b><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=759986 target=akztarg>Anglish Wildwood</a></b><br><i>Ranger of Luclin</i></td></td></tr>
